---
title: Baked Chicken Parmesan with DIY Marinara, Fresh Mozzarella, and Rigatoni
description: Chicken Parmesan is one of those dishes we could eat any night of the week: crispy chicken, melty cheese, tomato-y sauce—what’s not to love? The only obstacle to actually doing so is the cleanup it involves. We were determined to come up with a version that’s quicker and simpler, and we think we’ve just succeeded. The breadcrumb-topped chicken is simply baked in the oven, then nestled into a pan of marinara and served with melty cheese atop al dente rigatoni.
